## Git Instructions

- Always include "[Cursor] " in the commit message and PR title.
- Keep the messages short, concise and descriptive.
- The only non-letter characters allowed are parentheses ("()"), colons (":"), and hyphens ("-").
- Always use conventional commit messages.
- If the code change applies to the entire codebase, use "*" in the parenthesis.

## Usage

Commit Message Prefixes:
- "fix:" for bug fixes
- "feat:" for new features
- "perf:" for performance improvements
- "docs:" for documentation changes
- "style:" for formatting changes
- "refactor:" for code refactoring
- "test:" for adding missing tests
- "chore:" for maintenance tasks

## Message Rules

- Only use lowercase for commit messages
- Keep it concise
- Reference issue numbers when applicable

## Example commit messages

- [Cursor] feat(home): add faq section
- [Cursor] feat(footer): add copyright info
- [Cursor] fix(navbar): center buttons
- [Cursor] style(*): format all code using prettier
- [Cursor] docs(readme): add readme
- [Cursor] chore(deps): add jotai
- [Cursor] chore(deps): bump version
